40|$|<b>Swiss</b> <b>banking</b> is a 'generic name' for {{a system}} based on private banking and banking secrecy. In the {{introductory}} chapter we highlight the difference between <b>Swiss</b> <b>banking</b> and banking in the Switzerland's system. In the second chapter we present a more {{detailed description of the}} institution of banking secrecy, while in the third chapter we present the exceptions to it. The fourth chapter elaborates on the present and the future of <b>Swiss</b> <b>banking.</b> It is argued whether in the present circumstances banking secrecy has become disruptive to the further development of both <b>Swiss</b> <b>banking</b> and banking in Switzerland and whether <b>Swiss</b> <b>banking</b> will come to an end in the future...|$|R
